sentences: She was also the Sheriff of Kolkata (2001).
After prolonged illness Mitra died of a cardiac ailment on 3 January 2011, in Kolkata.

In 1941, Suchitra Mitra received a scholarship to Sangit Bhavana in Santiniketan, where she learnt Rabindra Sangeet from some of the greatest teachers  - Indira Devi Chaudhurani, Santidev Ghosh, and Sailajaranjan Majumdar.
Having obtained her diploma from Santiniketan, Suchitra Mitra returned to Calcutta in 1945.
In 1946, she earned her degree from Scottish Church College of the University of Calcutta.
Suchitra was considered to be one of the most versatile exponents of Rabindra Sangeet, and in recognition thereof she was awarded the Padma Shri by the Government of India in 1974.
Tagore Hymn Prize in 1945 from London Tagore Hymn Society.
Padma Shri in 1974 from the Government of India
Sangeet Natak Academy Award in 1986 from the Government of India
She retired in 1984 from Rabindra Bharati University as a professor and the Head of Rabindra Sangeet Department.
One of them, titled Suchitra Mitra (1993) by Raja Sen, went on to win the National Film Award for Best Cultural Film.
She became the first female Sheriff of Kolkata in 2001.

sentences: Suchitra Mitra (19 September 1924 – 3 January 2011) was an Indian singer, composer, artist exponent of Rabindra Sangeet or the songs of Bengal's poet laureate Rabindranath Tagore, professor, and the first woman Sheriff of Kolkata.
As an academic, she remained a professor and the Head of Rabindra Sangeet Department at the Rabindra Bharati University for many years.
Mitra was a playback singer in Bengali films (and acted in some as well)  and was associated for many years with the Indian People's Theatre Association.
In the same year, she co-founded Rabitirtha along with Dwijen Chowdhury (the name Rabitirtha was coined by renowned historian and Tagore scholar Professor Kalidas Nag).
She was the author of many books in Bengali on Rabindra Sangeet, and had recently directed her efforts towards compiling an encyclopaedia of Tagore's songs for students and researchers.
